        {
            "id": 6222151949943404,
            "definition": {
                "type": "note",
                "content": "This is a Datadog dashboard titled “Datadog Billing,” providing a detailed overview of resource usage and activities related to monitoring and billing. The main section is divided into three categories: APM, Logs, and Infrastructure.\n\nAt the top, several key indicators are displayed, including:\n- Containers\n- Ingested Spans\n- APM Hosts\n- Indexed Spans\n- Custom Metrics\n- Ingested Logs\n- Indexed Logs\n- Hosts\n\nBelow these indicators, there are detailed graphs showing the behavior of ingested spans, ingested logs, hosts, containers, custom metrics, and more over time. Additionally, a section on the left displays the billing monitors, indicating the status of alerts and OKs for different metrics, such as the number of ingested spans and logs, among others.\n\nThe “Billing Monitors” section shows active alerts and OKs, providing a quick view of areas that need attention.\n\nThis dashboard is an essential tool for monitoring and managing resource usage and associated costs, ensuring efficient operations and staying within budget.",
                "background_color": "white",
                "font_size": "16",
                "text_align": "left",
                "vertical_align": "top",
                "show_tick": false,
                "tick_pos": "50%",
                "tick_edge": "left",
